author: Photos by Willie Dempsey
title: PICTURES: Talented Kilkenny Minor hurlers and family step out in style to presentation night
text:
Kilkenny's Leinster minor hurling champions and All-Ireland runners-up stepped out in style to Langtons recently for their medal presentation night.
USE THE ARROWS OR 'NEXT' TO BROWSE THROUGH THE FULL GALLERY
Celebrating the County's first Leinster Minor hurling crown since 2021 after the young Cats overcame Dublin last May, with a 48th-minute goal from Ollie O'Donovan proving crucial.
Kilkenny needed extra time to get past the Clare challenge in the semi-final, and extra time was again needed in the final when Tipperary ran out two-point victors at UPMC Nowlan Park at the end of June.
Photographer Willie Dempsey was on hand to capture the night for the Kilkenny People/Kilkenny Live.
